column20: I really enjoyed how he would try to make himself available past his office hours.
Even though there were just lecture-style classes, they were taught very well and I got a lot out of them.
column21: Not just lectures but actual class participation exercises would've been helpful.

Making the hardest tests in the homework extra credit instead of part of the homework credit. That way students can get the feedback that they learned the required information about the homework and have the option to improve their algorithms if they have the time.

column20: Learning more of the basics of coding after Data Structures is always a plus when it comes to the major/
column21: Maybe giving some more pseudocode when it comes to some of the main topics covered in class? It can be very tricky trying to figure out some of the correlations between it and the material sometimes.

column20: The professor made the course super engaging. Offering questions, giving us examples, always visualizing. It helped that it was a small classroom.

column19: He would sometime overcomplicates the topic. But recitations made it easier to understand.
column20: The most beneficial is not mandatory to attend every class, as many classes are just repeats of each other and cover only 20 more minutes of content.
column21: If he checked his inbox more and recorded his lectures. Sometimes it would have helped just to be able to watch it, even if I was in the class.

column20: The classworks were very effective at reinforcing the topic materials. I almost wanted more classwork exercises to further improve my understanding.

column21: being able to see what I got wrong on hws

column20: The applications of these algorithms in all aspects of computer science in the industry
column21: More hands-on classwork going through actual problems together
